Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 14:38:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(history): R-based expectancy tracker

Replace the binary profit/loss marking with exit-level grading
(SL/BE/TP1/TP2/TP3) and compute true expectancy in R, modelling the
EA's 50/30/20 partial + breakeven management (max ~1.7R).

- db: add `exit` and `realized_r` columns to analyses
- api-spec: HistoryEntry gains exit/realizedR; PATCH outcome -> exit
- api-server: history PATCH validates and writes exit
- chart-analyzer: new expectancy.ts (R model + stats); History page
  shows Expectancy / Profit Factor / Win Rate / Total R + exit buttons

`realized_r` is left for MT5 to fill later with the precise R, which
overrides the modelled value.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
